1. HowTo add Class-Templates to Netbeans

- Open the menu Tools -> Templates
- Choose the PHP folder and click "Add..."
- Navigate to this folder ./class-templates/ and choose the templates you want to add
- After adding a new Template you propably have to rename it (sometimes its possible that the new
  added template is listet as "PHP File"
- You should add the templates to the PHP folder because you can only choose from categories
  apropriate for PHP projects (e. g. PHP, XML and Other)
  
2. HowTo add Code-Templates to Netbeans

- Open the menu Tools -> Options
- Choose Editor and there the tab Code Templates
- Select PHP as language and click Import
- Navigate to this folder ./code-templates/ and choose the zip file

Current Content of the Code Templates

- fc  (public function with no argument)
- fc1 (public function with one argument)
- fc2 (public function with two arguments)
- ut  (public function for unittests)
- utt (public function for unittests that expects an Exception

Removed Netbeans Code Templates

- cls (class template)
